Supervise administrative staff and ensure timely execution of daily operations and support services.
Travel & Accommodation Management

Lead and manage employee travel and accommodation arrangements (domestic and international).
Establish travel policies and ensure adherence to company guidelines and budgets.
Negotiate with travel agencies, hotels, and transport vendors for cost-effective and quality services.
Maintain travel MIS reports, expense tracking, and related documentation.
Vendor Management

Identify, evaluate, and manage vendors and service providers across admin, travel, transport, housekeeping, and facility management.
Negotiate contracts, manage service-level agreements (SLAs), and monitor vendor performance.
Develop and maintain long-term vendor relationships ensuring quality, efficiency, and cost optimization.
Manage procurement processes for administrative requirements and ensure timely renewals of AMC/service contracts.
Events & Employee Engagement

Plan and execute corporate events, annual gatherings, all hands, and employee engagement initiatives.
Coordinate logistics, vendor support, and budget management for all company-wide events.
Ensure smooth execution of events aligned with company culture and leadership expectations.
Factories & Labour Compliance

Coordinate administrative and statutory compliance activities for factory operations.
Liaise with HR, Legal, and Compliance teams to ensure adherence to labour laws, factory regulations, and safety norms.
Maintain documentation related to factory licenses, labour records, statutory audits, and inspections.
Oversee administrative arrangements for factory infrastructure, facilities, and staff welfare.
Coordination, Reporting & Leadership

Collaborate with management and cross-functional teams to align administrative processes with organizational goals.
Prepare periodic MIS reports related to travel, vendor performance, expenses, and compliance.
Manage and mentor the admin team, ensuring high standards of service delivery and operational excellence.
Continuously review and improve administrative systems, policies, and procedures.


Qualifications & Skills:

Graduate or Postgraduate in Business Administration / Management, or related discipline.
7–9 years of progressive experience in administrative operations, with exposure to travel, vendor management, and compliance functions.
Strong understanding of factory administration and labour law compliance.
Proficiency in MS Office and experience with ERP/Admin management tools.
Proven leadership, decision-making, and vendor negotiation skills.
Excellent communication, interpersonal, and organizational abilities.
Strong sense of ownership, accountability, and attention to detail.

